'''Bronislovas Lubys''' (8 October 1938 – 23 October 2011) was a [[Lithuania]]n entrepreneur, former [[Prime Minister of Lithuania]], signatory of the [[Act of the Re-Establishment of the State of Lithuania]], and businessman.

Lubys was born in [[Plungė]]. He was CEO and main shareholder of the Lithuanian company [[Achema]]. As of August 2008, he was the richest Lithuanian, according to the Lithuanian magazine ''[[Veidas]]''.<ref>{{cite journal| journal=[[Veidas]] |title=Turtingiausi lietuviai |first=Giedrė |last=Putelytė |author2=Milda Augustinaitytė | url=http://www.veidas.lt/wp-content/uploads/2008_turtuoliai_23.pdf |date=9 June 2008 |volume=23|language=lt}}</ref>

Lubys died of a heart attack while riding a bicycle in [[Druskininkai]] on 23 October 2011.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/lithuania/mire-vienas-itakingiausiu-lietuvos-verslininku-blubys.d?id=51003389 |title=

Mirė vienas įtakingiausių Lietuvos verslininkų B.Lubys |first= Rasa |last=Lukaitytė |author2=Justina Juršytė |publisher=[[Delfi.lt]] |date=23 October 2010|language=lt}}</ref>

