[[File:Cristián Reitze.jpg|thumb|Cristián Reitze]] '''Cristián Reitze Campos''' is a [[Chile]]an [[politician]] and [[businessman]]. He is a member of the [[Humanist Party of Chile]] (PH) and acted as president of the party. In 1993 he was one of the candidates for the [[president of Chile|presidency of Chile]], representing the [[Humanist Green Alliance]] (Alianza Humanista Verde, AHV), but only gained 1.17% of the total valid votes; [[Eduardo Frei Ruiz-Tagle]] was eventually elected.<ref name=presidencial>{{cite web|url=http://www.elecciones.gob.cl/SitioHistorico/paginas/1993/presidencial1v/pais/candidatos/total/1.htm|title=Votación País Presidencial 1993|work=elecciones.gob.cl|language=Spanish|accessdate=2010-11-26|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110709142522/http://elecciones.gob.cl/SitioHistorico/paginas/1993/presidencial1v/pais/candidatos/total/1.htm|archivedate=2011-07-09|df=}}</ref>
In the [[Chilean parliamentary election, 1997|1997 parliamentary elections]], he was a candidate for senator for [[Santiago Metropolitan Region|Santiago Poniente]]. After the elections, he continued to work inside the Humanist Party, and he dedicated himself to his family's business of selling cars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diario.elmercurio.cl/detalle/index.asp?id={eef3c6ee-b758-42df-8281-9363ba123712}|title=Los candidatos olvidados|work=El Mercurio|date=November 11, 2006|accessdate=2010-11-26}}</ref>
