'''New Europe Market (NEM)''' is an annual marketing conference, market and screenings event held in Dubrovnik, and run by the Croatian company Mediavision Ltd.<ref name="new-market-for-cee">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaltveurope.net/29027/new-market-for-cee|title=New market for CEE|publisher=digitaltveurope.net|accessdate=2015-11-10}}</ref> The focal idea behind the event is the creation of a platform where media, telecommunications and marketing professionals can share their knowledge and experience during the conference and networking events. The conference is addressed to [[Free-to-air|FTAs]], [[Pay television|Pay-TV channels]], [[Cable television|cable operators]], [[Satellite television|satellite operators]], [[IPTV]], [[Production company|production]] and [[Film distribution|distribution]] companies, [[Media agency|media]] and [[Advertising agency|marketing]] agencies and specialists. NEM focuses on the [[Central and Eastern Europe|CEE region]], but the event attendees come from all over the world,.<ref name="neweuropemarket">{{cite web|url= http://neweumarket.com/about-nem/|title= About – New Europe Market|publisher=neweumarket.com|accessdate=2015-11-09}}</ref>{{external media | width = 210px | headerimage=[[File:Ivo_Josipovi%C4%87_election_2009-2010_left.jpg|210px]] | float = right
| video1 =[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=McAgDrCtG50 New Europe Market (NEM) 2013: Ivo Josipovic's welcome speech]<ref name="Ivo Josipovic welcome speech">{{cite web | title =New Europe Market (NEM) 2013: Ivo Josipovic's welcome speech | work = | publisher =New Europe Market | url =https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=McAgDrCtG50| accessdate =November 9, 2015 }}</ref>
}}

The first New Europe Market was a four-day event held in May 2013 in Dubrovnik and gathered representatives from 250 companies. The event was held under the auspices of the [[President of Croatia|President of the Republic of Croatia]], [[Ivo Josipović]],.<ref name="ivo-josipovic">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/international-tv-execs-attend-new-519440|title=International TV Execs Attend New Europe Market Launch, Discuss Boosting Business|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=2015-11-09}}</ref> Topics of discussion ranged from “Sport migration from Public to Pay TV” to “Channel Distribution”.

In 2014 New Europe Market included, for the first time, screenings and production workshops. During the conference [[HBO Europe|HBO Adria]] revealed a replica of [[Iron Throne (A Song of Ice and Fire)|the Iron Throne]], from [[Game of Thrones]], which was a very popular tourist attraction in Dubrovnik, where  Game Of Thrones was partly filmed,.<ref name="nem-iron-throne">{{cite web|url=http://dubrovacki.hr/clanak/63796/game-of-thrones-iron-throne-in-dubrovnik|title=Game of Thrones Iron Throne in Dubrovnik|publisher=dubrovacki.hr|accessdate=2015-11-09}}</ref><ref name="nem-hbo-sungarden">{{cite web|url=http://www.incentivetravel.co.uk/news/hotel/20513-sun-gardens-dubrovnik-hosts-hbo-and-the-food-network-at-this-year-s-nem-conference|title=Chris Dziadul Reports: NEM 2015 review|publisher=incentivetravel.co.uk|accessdate=2015-11-10}}</ref> Discussions during the NEM concerned topics like trends in global promotion of local content or developments of cloud technology<ref name=videoage>{{cite news|title=Underpenetrated Region Offers Opportunities For Indie Cinema|url=http://www.videoageinternational.com/pdfUploads/issuearchives/2014/2014_34_03.pdf|accessdate=2015-11-10|work=Videoage|page=30|date=April 2014}}</ref>

The third edition of New Europe Market introduced discussions on the economic challenges in the CEE region for the media industry,<ref name="nem-n1info">{{cite web|url=http://hr.n1info.com/a54692/Vijesti/Nigel-McCrery-Svijet-se-mijenja-moramo-se-prilagoditi-ili-cemo-nestati.html|title=Svijet se mijenja - moramo se prilagoditi ili ćemo nestati|publisher=n1info.com|accessdate=2015-11-10}}</ref> new TV metrics and the future of [[second screen]].<ref name="nem-broadband-review">{{cite web|url=http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2015/06/12/chris-dziadul-reports-nem-2015-review/|title=Chris Dziadul Reports: NEM 2015 review|publisher=broadbandtvnews.com|accessdate=2015-11-10}}</ref><ref name=poslovni>{{cite news|title=Trebat će nam nove metode mjerenja gledanosti televizije|url=http://www.poslovni.hr/marketing-i-mediji/trebat-ce-nam-nove-metode-mjerenja-gledanosti-televizije-297296|accessdate=2015-11-10|work=Poslovni|date=10 June 2015}}</ref> NEM 2015 again hosted screenings, as well as a production panel with guests like [[Tom Fontana]]<ref name="nem-tom-fontana">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvmasmagazine.com/2015/06/19/en-nem-tom-fontana-anuncio-su-nueva-serie/?lang=en|title=In NEM Tom Fontana announced his new series|publisher=tvmasmagazine.com|accessdate=2015-11-10}}</ref> and [[Nigel McCrery]]. For the first time NEM also hosted a session featuring a TV star, with [[Tim Daly]]<ref name="nem-tim-daly-tvmas">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvmasmagazine.com/2015/06/21/nem-tim-daly-estuvo-encantado-en-dubrovnik/?lang=en|title=NEM: Tim Daly enchanted Dubrovnik|publisher=tvmasmagazine.com|accessdate=2015-11-10}}</ref> of [[Madam Secretary (TV series)|Madam Secretary]] taking stage for a keynote interview,.<ref name="nem-tim-daly">{{cite web|url= http://www.croatiaweek.com/madam-secretary-star-in-croatia-for-qa-at-nem-conference|title=‘Madam Secretary’ Star in Croatia for Q&A at NEM Conference|publisher= croatiaweek.com|accessdate=2015-11-09}}</ref>

The 4th edition of NEM brought together more than 300 companies and 1000+ participants from all over the world that took part in 10 panel discussions, two presentations and countless networking opportunities. NEM 2016 was marked by the global premiere of the series ''The Paper'', keynote speech from Christoph Mainusch, co-CEO of Central European Media Enterprises and executive director and & CEO of Nova Group, Vice`s announcement of expansion in the region, Podravka`s presentation of its new series ''Croatia’s Finest'' with MasterChef winner Dhruv Baker as well as the released information about a new partnership Ginx has finalized with Sky and ITV involving the launch of the first UK 24-hour eSport Channel.<ref>http://www.formatbiz.it/post.php?id=2806</ref>

NEM staff includes 12 young people (changing every year), students of journalism, media, production etc., who gain knowledge and experience from working in their related branches.  In this way NEM strengthens ties and connections between academic and business sectors whilst also developing new ideas and standards.

